{"nodes": [{"id": "architecture_device_proxy", "label": "Server-side Device Proxy", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The WiiM HTTP API has no auth and a self-signed cert, so the browser never contacts the device directly; all device traffic goes through authenticated Route Handlers."}, {"id": "architecture_request_lifecycle", "label": "Request Lifecycle (middleware \u2192 guard \u2192 Zod \u2192 device call \u2192 transport \u2192 parse)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "architecture_ssrf_guard", "label": "SSRF Guard (resolve \u2192 LAN IP-check \u2192 pin)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "DNS-resolve, verify private/LAN range, then pin the connection to the resolved IP \u2014 blocks DNS rebinding and keeps the proxy from reaching public or cloud-metadata hosts."}, {"id": "architecture_wiim_device_layer", "label": "src/lib/wiim Device Layer", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "architecture_dlna_library", "label": "NAS/DLNA Library Module (src/lib/dlna)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The WiiM HTTP API cannot browse content, so the dashboard talks to the UPnP/DLNA media server directly; browse/art requests reuse the SSRF guard constrained to the configured media host."}, {"id": "architecture_avtransport_playback", "label": "AVTransport-driven NAS Playback", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The httpapi setPlayerCmd:playlist push ignores the start index and resumes a stale playlist cursor (starts mid-album), so NAS playback drives the WiiM's own UPnP MediaRenderer (SetAVTransportURI + Play + SetNextAVTransportURI) instead \u2014 ordered, first-track start, real DIDL metadata."}, {"id": "architecture_lastfm_scrobbler", "label": "Last.fm Background Scrobbler (poller)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Runs in the Node process (started from instrumentation.ts register()) so scrobbling works with no browser tab open; globalThis guards double-start; polls every 15 s per enabled device."}, {"id": "architecture_lastfm_love", "label": "Love via Last.fm track.love/unlove", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The WiiM HTTP API has no native favorite/like command \u2014 the WiiM app's heart calls each streaming service's cloud API which the server can't reach \u2014 so the dashboard's heart is wired through Last.fm instead."}, {"id": "architecture_lastfm_ignored_scrobble_detection", "label": "Ignored-Scrobble Detection (scrobbles.@attr.ignored)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Last.fm returns HTTP 200 even when it silently drops a scrobble (e.g. artist 'Various Artists', its compilation anti-spam rule), so the client inspects scrobbles.@attr.ignored and logs the real outcome; ignored plays are not retried because a re-submit would be dropped again."}, {"id": "architecture_sleep_timer", "label": "Server-side Sleep Timer Registry", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Kept in the Node process so the scheduled pause fires even with no browser open; the snapshot exposes the expiry for a live countdown."}, {"id": "architecture_nas_queue_advancer", "label": "NAS Play-Queue Advancer (nas-queue.ts)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "UPnP AVTransport only holds a current + one next URI, so an interval polls GetPositionInfo and loads the following track via SetNextAVTransportURI for ordered whole-album playback; also the source of truth for proxied cover art."}, {"id": "architecture_capability_detection", "label": "Capability Detection & Caching", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "detectCapabilities probes once on add/refresh and caches the result on the device row so the 3 s poll loop never re-probes."}, {"id": "architecture_preset_cache", "label": "30 s Preset-List Cache", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Shared between the poll and the 12 preset-art image requests to avoid an N+1 request storm on the embedded device."}, {"id": "architecture_auth_stack", "label": "Auth & Hardening Stack (src/lib/auth)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "architecture_deployment", "label": "Docker Standalone Deployment (non-root via gosu)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Entrypoint fixes data-dir ownership so bind-mounts (e.g. Unraid appdata) work, then drops to uid 1001 via gosu; the app never runs as root."}], "edges": [{"source": "architecture_request_lifecycle", "target": "architecture_ssrf_guard", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_wiim_device_layer", "target": "architecture_ssrf_guard", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_dlna_library", "target": "architecture_ssrf_guard", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_dlna_library", "target": "architecture_avtransport_playback", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_avtransport_playback", "target": "architecture_nas_queue_advancer", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_lastfm_scrobbler", "target": "architecture_lastfm_ignored_scrobble_detection", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_lastfm_scrobbler", "target": "architecture_lastfm_love", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_capability_detection", "target": "docs_wiim_api_getstatusex", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_wiim_device_layer", "target": "docs_wiim_api_httpapi_transport", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_wiim_device_layer", "target": "docs_wiim_api_sub_out", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.95, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_preset_cache", "target": "docs_wiim_api_getpresetinfo", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_auth_stack", "target": "security_session_hmac", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_auth_stack", "target": "security_csrf_double_submit", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_auth_stack", "target": "security_rate_limiting", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_request_lifecycle", "target": "security_csrf_double_submit", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "ARCHITECTURE.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "architecture_request_lifecycle", "target": "security_csp_headers", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.